cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically with the effect of grammatical gender on word representations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method to improve the quality of word embeddings by removing gender bias, which involves training a machine learning model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper addresses a common issue in natural language processing and proposes a solution using AI techniques. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural network-based word embeddings and proposes a method to modify the training process to remove gender bias. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper touches upon the societal issue of gender bias in language and proposes a solution to mitigate it.
